{
  "stem": "9503.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "One of the reasons that I really want to do the tape is for posterity, but also for my personal posterity for the children.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And-- and there have been remarks-- so now we will learn what this is going to be, what this was like.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] At this point, I feel almost that we have an obligation to talk, and I do volunteer to go to schools and talk about it.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But it's much easier to talk to strangers, strange kids, and answer their questions.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I usually tell them, you can ask me anything you want.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "You know, I'll answer unless I really feel that it's not appropriate.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "It doesn't give me difficulty.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I can go back and have lunch.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] it's just the-- the kind of an experience that I think is so out of the-- the realm of experiences that it maybe is-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] you have to learn to accept it, that it's part of you, rather than denying it.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And once it becomes part of you, it becomes a sad part of you.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] that doesn't mean that you can't, you know, look, it's sunshine out.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I enjoy my family.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I enjoy my work, love my husband, love my family, my grandchildren.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I'm not living life in the past, but it is part of me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And-- and every once in a while-- I mean, I used to-- if I was driving my car and-- and the-- the railroad gate would go down and there would be a freight train, I mean, I would shiver.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'd have to turn on the radio and-- and think of-- of different things.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's not the case anymore.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
